quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  35,4,"And if they disbelieve you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, surely messengers before you were also disbelieved. And to Allah all matters <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ibn Amer, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i, Ya’qub and Khalaf read it as: “…all matters return.”</span>
  35,5,"O mankind, indeed the promise of Allah is true, so let not the Earlier Life deceive you, and let not the Deceiver deceive you regarding Allah."
  35,6,"Indeed, Satan is an enemy to youpl , so take him as an enemy; indeed, he only invites his party to be among the fellows of the Blaze."
  35,7,"For those who have denied is a severe punishment, while for those who have attained faith and have done righteous deeds is forgiveness and a supreme reward."
  35,8,"What about the one whose evil deed was adorned for him and so he came to regard it as good? Allah misguides whomever He wills and He guides whomever He wills, so <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Abu Ja’far read it as: “…so do not waste your self sorrowing over them;”</span>
  35,9,"And Allah is the One Who sent the <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ibn Kathir, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i, and Khalaf read it as: “wind”.</span>,footnotes:2:A grammatical shift from 3<sup><small>rd</small></sup> person to 1<sup><small>st</small></sup> person.
  35,10,"Whoever wants might—to Allah belongs all might. To Him ascends good speech, and righteous work lifts it up. But as for those who scheme evil, there is a severe punishment, and the scheming of those is bound to fail."